6. When to Use WebFlux vs. MVC
  Critical Warning: The "Blocking" Poison
  If you call a blocking method (like Thread.sleep() or a standard JPA repository) inside a WebFlux flow, you will freeze the entire server.
  Since there are only a few threads, blocking one of them can stop all incoming requests.
  
  Rule: Never block an event loop thread. If you must use a blocking library, run it on a separate BoundedElastic scheduler.
